ll-team-one-for-the-ages/|title=The Tufts Daily|work=The Tufts Daily}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ase.tufts.edu/athletics/old/menFootball/press/2004-2005/firstgamebuzz.html|title=Tufts|publisher=}}</ref>  The Jumbos compete at the [[NCAA Division III]] level and have been members of the [[New England Small College Athletic Conference]] (NESCAC) since the conference's formation in 1971. The football team plays its home game at [[Ellis Oval]] on the Tufts campus in [[Medford, Massachusetts]]. [[Jay Civetti]] has been the team's head coach since 2011. One Tufts player, [[William Grinnell]], has been inducted into the [[College Football Hall of Fame]].\n\n\n==Annual results==\nTeam records from 1875 to 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gotuftsjumbos.com/sports/fball/records|title=Tufts University Football Program Records|publisher=}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Tufts Jumbos|Year|Record|Captain|Coach}}\n|-\n| 1875 || 2\u20131 || Luman Aldrich || Luman Aldrich\n|-\n| 1876\u201377 || 1\u20130\u20131 || Luman Aldrich || Luman Aldrich\n|-\n| 1877 || 0\u20133 || Scott Campbell || Scott Campbell\n|-\n| 1878\u201383 || colspan=\"3\"| No Formal Games \n|-\n| 1884 || 2\u20134\u20131 || Dwight Griswold || Dwight Griswold\n|-\n| 1885 || 2\u20133<br />(or 2\u20134<ref name=\"tufts\"/>) || F.P. Chapman || F.P. Chapman\n|-\n| 1886 || 0\u20138 || James Gallety || James Gallety\n|-\n| 1887 || 3\u20136 || Durkee || Durkee\n|-\n| 1888 || colspan=\"3\"| No Formal Games\n|-\n| 1889 || 3\u20131 || Martin || Martin\n|-\n| 1890 || 2\u20133 || Charles Stover || Charles Stover\n|-\n| 1891 || 7\u20131 || Wilfred Russ || Wilfred Russ\n|-\n| 1892 || 8\u20132 || Wilfred Russ || A.G. Baillet\n|-\n| 1893 || 4\u20137 || [[Charles Dow Clark]] || Haskell\n|-\n| 1894 || 6\u20135 || Lane || Hamlin\n|-\n| 1895 || 8\u20135 || W.D. Smith || Newell\n|-\n| 1896 || 2\u20136\u20131 || Horace Davis || Newell\n|-\n| 1897 || 6\u20137 || Carpenter || [[Joshua Damon Upton|J.D.