the proper working solution, supported by just a few.</ref>\n! [[Distributed hash table|DHT]] <ref name=\"dht\" group=\"Note\">DHT permits use of trackerless torrents (with supporting clients) to resume normal torrents when their tracker is down. However, some trackers that register their users for keeping tabs on fair usage (such as a ratio of bytes downloaded to uploaded) may not reliably measure and update usage for users employing DHT.</ref>\n! [[Peer exchange]]\n! [[BitTorrent protocol encryption|Encryption]]\n! [[UDP tracker]]\n! [[Local Peer Discovery|LPD]]\n! [[Proxy server]]\n|-\n| [[ABC (Yet Another BitTorrent Client)|ABC]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|-\n| [[Acquisition (software)|Acquisition]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|-\n| [[BitComet]]\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes2}} Separate download\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes|HTTP 1.1, [[SOCKS]]4-4a-5}}\n|-\n| [[BitLet]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|-\n| [[BitLord]]\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes|HTTP 1.1, SOCKS4-4a-5}}\n|-\n| [[BitTornado]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}<ref name=\"linuxtracker\" group=Note>Tracker included with Linux binaries and with source, but not with Windows binary.</ref>\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|-\n| [[BitTorrent (software)|BitTorrent]] 5, Mainline\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}<ref name=\"linuxtracker\" group=Note />\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n|-\n| BitTorrent 6\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}<ref name=\"exchange\" group=Note>Exchanging with BT 6 and \u03bcTorrent clients (and now MooPolice).</ref>\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes|HTTP(S), SOCKS4-5}}\n|-\n| [[BitTyrant]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}{{Citation needed|date=December 2008}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}<ref group=Note>It's UDP based, an experimental feature and only supported by other Azureus based clients.</ref>\n| {{yes}}<ref name=\"dht_not_compatible\" group=Note>Has its own DHT, a mainline-DHT compatible implementation is available as plugin.</ref>\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|-\n| [[Blog Torrent]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|-\n| [[Deluge (software)|Deluge]]\n| {{yes}}\n| {{partial}}<ref group=Note>This is done manually. Right click an item and select \"Force Re-Check\". This will trigger preload. Note, if deluge is restarted before preload finishes, it will continue downloading torrent content.</ref>\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes|HTTP(S), SOCKS4-5}}\n|-\n| [[FlashGet]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|-\n| [[Free Download Manager]]\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|-\n| [[KTorrent]]\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{partial}}\n| {{yes|HTTP, SOCKS4-5}}\n|-\n| [[LimeWire]]\n| {{partial}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|-\n| [[Meerkat Bittorrent Client]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|-\n| [[MLDonkey]]\n| {{yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mldonkey.sourceforge.net/forums/viewtopic.php?p=32169 |title=MLDonkey 3.1.3 release notes |publisher=Forum mldonkey.sourceforge.net |date= |accessdate=13 February 2013}}</ref>\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|-\n| [[\u03bcTorrent]]\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.apk20.com/apk/5903/ |title=\u03bcTorrent 3.13 Apk For Android |publisher=apk20.com |date= |accessdate=22 November 2015}}</ref>\n| {{yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://forum.utorrent.com/viewtopic.php?id=11463 |title=\u03bcTorrent 1.6 released |publisher=Forum.utorrent.com |date= |accessdate=28 November 2009}}</ref>\n| {{yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://filesharefreak.com/tutorials/utorrent-make-your-own-bittorrent-tracker/ |title=uTorrent: Make Your Own BitTorrent Tracker |publisher=Filesharefreak.com |date= |accessdate=28 November 2009}}</ref>\n| {{yes}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.utorrent.com/setup_guide.php |title=Setting up \u03bcTorrent for your internet connection |publisher=www.utorrent.com |date= |accessdate=28 November 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090315005429/http://www.utorrent.com/setup_guide.php |archive-date=15 March 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}<ref name=\"\u03bcTorrent 2.0 beta\">{{cite web|url=https://forum.utorrent.com/viewtopic.php?id=60602|title=\u03bcTorrent Community Forums}}</ref>\n| {{yes}}<ref group=Note>\u03bcTorrent's [https://www.utorrent.com/faq.php#What_is_DHT.3F DHT implementation] is the same as Mainline and BitComet's, but unfortunately this is incompatible with Azureus's implementation.</ref>\n| {{yes}}<ref name=\"exchange\" group=Note />\n| {{yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://torrentfreak.com/how-to-encrypt-bittorrent-traffi