ransmission-Qt |publisher=Sourceforge.net |date= |accessdate=27 April 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120825050551/http://sourceforge.net/projects/trqtw/ |archive-date=25 August 2012 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>unofficial build cfpp2p GitHub transmission {{cite web|url=https://github.com/cfpp2p/transmission/commit/c81be4700920ead21771f2fb2f6e2f099896a02d |title=magnet download not verified for existing data |publisher=github.com |date= |accessdate=27 April 2016}}</ref>\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}<ref>https://github.com/transmission/transmission/blob/20119f006ca0f3a13245b379c74254c92f372910/libtransmission/peer-msgs.c#L2454</ref>\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}<ref group=Note>Exchanges with \u03bcTorrent and Azureus peers.</ref>\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}<ref>Proxy support was removed in version 2.12: {{cite web|url=https://trac.transmissionbt.com/ticket/3688 |title=Ticket #3688 |publisher=trac.transmissionbt.com |date= |accessdate=11 June 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Tribler]]\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes2|Uses [[Peer-to-peer|P2P]] [[onion routing]] to provide anonymity.}}\n|-\n| [[Vuze]] <small>(formerly Azureus)</small>\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}<ref group=Note>Since version 2.5.0.2. It's UDP based, an experimental feature and only supported by other Azureus clients.</ref>\n| {{yes}}<ref name=\"dht_not_compatible\" group=Note />\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes|Plugin}}\n| {{yes|HTTP(S)?, SOCKS4-4a-5}}\n|-\n| [[Xunlei]]\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes|HTTP, SOCKS5, FTP}}\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n! BitTorrent client\n! Magnet URI\n! Preload Magnet metadata\n! Super-seeding\n! Embedded tracker\n! UPnP\n! NAT Port Mapping Protocol\n! NAT traversal\n! DHT\n! Peer exchange\n! Encryption\n! UDP tracker\n! LPD\n! Proxy server\n|}\n\n=== Features II ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width: 100%; text-align: center; font-size: smaller;\"\n|-\n! BitTorrent client\n! [[Cache (computing)|Cache]] <ref name=\"cache\" group=Note>Reduces disk usage, file fragmentation (in case it is not preallocated) and latencies via larger written blocks and cached data for hash checking finished pieces.</ref>\n! Hash [[Webseeding|Web seeding]]\n! HTTP [[Webseeding|Web seeding]]\n! [[Broadcatching|Broad-catching]] ([[RSS]])\n! Prioritization\n! Selective downloads\n! Sequential downloading\n! [[SOCKS]]\n! Tracker exchange <ref name=\"tex\">Tracker exchange spec: [http://www.bittorrent.org/beps/bep_0028.html BEP 28]</ref>\n! Remote control via web\n! [[BitTorrent (protocol)#Indexing|Search engine]]\n! Auto updates\n! Reviews and Comments\n! Notes\n|-\n| [[ABC (Yet Another BitTorrent Client)|ABC]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes2}} Separate download\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Acquisition (software)|Acquisition]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| 3 torrents max, infinite when registered\n|-\n| [[BitComet]]\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}<ref>Supports the [http://www.getright.com/seedtorrent.html Getright Webseeding spec] since v1.14, see [http://wiki.bitcomet.com/Making_torrents_with_BitComet#Web_Seeding BitComet Wiki]</ref>\n| {{beta}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}<ref group=Note>Called [http://wiki.bitcomet.com/preview_while_downloading \"preview mode\"]</ref>\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n|{{partial|Built-in Web browser}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| Portable version available\n|-\n| [[BitLet]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n|-\n| [[BitLord]]\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no