rists |title=Some Malaysians calling for ban on Chinese tourists |last=Solhi |first=Farah | name-list-format = vanc |date=26 January 2020 |work=[[New Straits Times]] |access-date=12 February 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200127152306/https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2020/01/559942/some-malaysians-calling-ban-chinese-tourists |archive-date=27 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"7hjPP\">{{cite news |title=Calm urged as anti-Chinese sentiment felt in New Zealand |url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12304816 |access-date=6 February 2020 |work=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200206014546/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12304816 |archive-date=6 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"1q0pE\">{{cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2020/01/31/coronavirus-chinese-xenophobia-racism-misinformation/2860391001/ |title=Coronavirus is spreading. And so is anti-Chinese sentiment and xenophobia. |first1=Marco |last1=della Cava |first2=Kristin |last2=Lam | name-list-format = vanc |work=[[USA Today]] |access-date=5 February 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200203011355/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2020/01/31/coronavirus-chinese-xenophobia-racism-misinformation/2860391001/ |archive-date=3 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"EIiOY\">{{cite news |title=Not Enough Doctors in Daegu: As Virus Cases Rise, South Korea's Response Is criticized |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/not-enough-doctors-in-daegu-as-virus-cases-rise-south-koreas-response-is-criticized-11582547600 |work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |date=24 February 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"69eLl\">{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/sarahkim/2020/01/30/coronavirus-racism-asian-communities/ |title=As The Coronavirus Spreads, So Does Racism \u2013 Both Against And Within Asian Communities |last=Kim |first=Sarah | name-list-format = vanc |work=[[Forbes]] |access-date=2 February 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200202205424/https://www.forbes.com/sites/sarahkim/2020/01/30/coronavirus-racism-asian-communities/ |archive-date=2 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"05O7n\">{{cite web |title=London Racially Motivated Assault due to Coronavirus |url=https://www.itv.com/news/london/2020-03-04/hunt-for-racist-coronavirus-attackers-police-release-cctv-after-oxford-street-assault/ |work=[[ITV News]] |access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"pHQ6A\">{{cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/02/21/europe/ukraine-wuhan-bus-coronavirus-intl/index.html |title=Protesters attack buses carrying Wuhan evacuees in Ukraine |publisher=[[CNN.com|CNN]] |date=21 February 2020 |access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"trt33408\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.trtworld.com/turkey/turkish-plane-carrying-wuhan-evacuees-lands-in-ankara-33408 |title=Turkish plane carrying Wuhan evacuees lands in Ankara |date=1 February 2020 |work=[[TRT World]] News |publisher=Turkish Radio and Television Corporation |access-date=3 February 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200203152227/https://www.trtworld.com/turkey/turkish-plane-carrying-wuhan-evacuees-lands-in-ankara-33408 |archive-date=3 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"NYT-20200326\">{{cite news |last=McNeil, Jr. |first=Donald G. |title=The U.S. Now Leads the World in Confirmed Coronavirus Cases \u2013 Following a series of missteps, the nation is now the epicenter of the pandemic. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/26/health/usa-coronavirus-cases.html |date=26 March 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"guardian29032020\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/29/china-coronavirus-anti-foreigner-feeling-imported-cases |title='They see my blue eyes then jump back' \u2013 China sees a new wave of xenophobia |first1=Lily |last1=Kuo |first2=Helen |last2=Davidson| name-list-format = vanc |date=29 March 2020 |work=The Guardian}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"diario6April\">{{cite web |title=Espa\u00f1a registra un aumento del 47% en la mortalidad pero los expertos piden tiempo para relacionarlo con el coronavirus |url=https://www.eldiario.es/sociedad/Espana-registra-mortalidad-relacionarlo-coronavirus_0_1013849053.html |access-date=7 April 2020 |language=es |date=6 April 2020 |first=Oriol Sol\u00e9 |last=Altimira |first2=Ra\u00fal |last2=S\u00e1nchez| name-list-format = vanc }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"AFPhigh\">{{cite news |title=WHO says global risk of China virus is 'high' |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/world/2020/01/27/who-says-global-risk-of-china-virus-is-039high039 |accessdate=18 April 2020 |agency=[[Agence France-Presse]] |date=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"KesslerApril17\">{{cite news |last1=Kessler |first1=Glenn |title=Trump's false claim that the WHO said the coronavirus was 'not communicable' |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2020/04/17/trumps-false-claim-that-who-said-coronavirus-was-not-communicable/ |accessdate=18 April 2020 |work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=17 April 2020 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/7Pgq4 |archivedate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"KennedyJanuary30\">{{cite news |last1=Kennedy |first1=Merrit |title=WHO Declares Coronavirus Outbreak A Global Health Emergency |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2020/01/30/798894428/who-declares-coronavirus-outbreak-a-global-health-emergency |accessdate=18 April 2020 |publisher=[[NPR]] |date=30 January 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"KuoJanuary21\">{{cite news |last1=Kuo |first1=Lily |title=China confirms human-to-human transmission of coronavirus |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/20/coronavirus-spreads-to-beijing-as-china-confirms-new-cases |accessdate=18 April 2020 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=21 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n</references>\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Sister project links|voy=2019\u20132020 